<br>
If you look at the lower level groups, amonst all the twinks you'll see quite a few people in banded/bronze, possibly with a nice item or two for their level that someone gave or sold to them. The problem is the NRo-Oasis-LOIO-OT path is nice if you're a twink and don't need to earn a lot of money or to get some of the better drops. But if you're starting fresh you've got to hit the dungeons, which are now grossly underpopulated. IF you do get a group in runnyeye, chances are you'll end up with two blackened alloy sleeves instead of a full suit. If you're lucky you'll find a buyer who'll give you slightly more than the vendor price for the extra.<br>
<br>
Likewise dieing in a highly populated dungeon really isn't that big of a deal, just carefully walk through the overcamped dungeon until you get back to where you fell. Total party whipeout in an underpopulated dungeon? Hope some high levels are camping the entrance next door in SOLB and are willing to help you get your body's back. I really wish I would have been around in the days when you could actually find people in remote dungeons.<br>
<br>
If you haven't got high level help, I imagine EQ can be quite daunting for a new player now. Standing next to supertwink and wonding why you're doing half his damage. Not being able to find a PC buyer for anything you can loot (sometimes even newbie treasures like bonechips are hard to sell. I don't even bother to try to sell bat wings anymore, I just trade them for binds/buffs). <br>
<br>
I honesty think all the low level changes will help the new player more than the twinks. Someone's alt can usually call a high level friend for a rez. A group of true newbies don't have that option right now, but with the new spells, they can at least get something.<br>
